<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="223" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[707,1193,194,507]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,851,194,215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in honor of the noted coleopterist and collector of the unique 
<typeStatus box="[1073,1155,221,242]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">holotype</typeStatus>
, the late William F. Barr (Westcott and Merickel 2012).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="223" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[707,1193,194,507]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,845,274,295]" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">Discussion.</emphasis>
This is arguably one of the most beautiful species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1833" box="[902,980,300,322]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[902,980,300,322]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">Brachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[1014,1090,300,321]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">Mexico</collectingRegion>
. The short lateral carina on the elytra of this and the following species is unusual among previously described species in the genus, with only 
<taxonomicName authority="Hespenheide" authorityName="Hespenheide" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intervallorum">
<emphasis box="[982,1193,379,401]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">Brachys intervallorum</emphasis>
Hespenheide
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Waterhouse" authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1889" box="[850,1144,406,428]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[850,1016,406,428]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">Brachys simplex</emphasis>
Waterhouse
</taxonomicName>
, and the following species having partial carinae, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fisher" authorityName="Fisher" authorityYear="1922" box="[707,948,459,481]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgidus">
<emphasis box="[707,877,459,481]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">Brachys fulgidus</emphasis>
Fisher
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hespenheide" authorityName="Hespenheide" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exquisitus">
<emphasis box="[1004,1193,459,481]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="223">Brachys exquisitus</emphasis>
Hespenheide
</taxonomicName>
lacking carinae altogether.
</paragraph>
